A vast, spiraling descent into a dark digital inferno rendered in Dante's classical style but reimagined as vintage 1950s illustration. Multiple circular levels of a hellish data center descend into an abyss, each ring populated by tormented server racks wreathed in orange flames and tangled cables that snake like tortured souls. Small figures in period business attire tumble between levels, surrounded by floating envelopes and scattered documents caught in thermal updrafts. The color palette features deep crimsons, burnt oranges, and shadowy blacks with touches of aged sepia and cream, giving it the appearance of a weathered mid-century magazine cover illustration with visible print texture and slight color misregistration.
